close_reason: Corrected the invalid verb-first-scope config invocation in MERGE_SAFETY.md and AGENT_GUIDE.md to the canonical 'pm config project set ids_token_length 6' form; verified all remaining docs use scope-first ordering via repo-wide grep.
body: "## Defect\nMERGE_SAFETY.md (PR#617) recommended `pm config set project ids.token_length 6`. The config grammar puts the scope BEFORE the verb (`pm config project set <key> <value>`), so the documented command parses \"project\" as the key and exits 2 with invalid_argument_value — an agent following the merge-safety guidance hits a guaranteed usage error at the exact moment it is adopting collision safety. Canonical form used everywhere else in docs/CONFIGURATION.md: `pm config project set ids_token_length 6` (scope-first; `pm config set <dotted.or.underscore.key>` without scope also works and defaults to project scope).\n\n## Fix\nBoth sites corrected to the canonical scope-first form: docs/MERGE_SAFETY.md entropy-budget bullet + docs/AGENT_GUIDE.md multi-branch section."
